Tokyo 2020 would be “grateful” if Group of Seven countries could support the Summer Games going ahead as planned, Tokyo 2020 organising committee president Seiko Hashimoto told a news conference on Friday. She added that the organising committee had set up a new vaccination centre for Olympics-related staff in Tokyo. The Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games, which was postponed once due to the global spread of the coronavirus, is scheduled to start on July 23. G7 leaders are meeting this weekend in Britain. Video Of The Day: CAS Rachel Shebesh and athlete Asbel Kiprop share their mental health journeys